original: Forssenius, Gunnar Torsten, advokat, Göteborg, f. 30/12/03 i Gbg av byggmäst. Johannes Andersson o. Anna Andersson-Forssenius. G. 42 m. Dagmar Sjöbring. Barn: Lars f. 43, Maud. 44. — Studiex. i Gbg 23, jur. kand. i Upps. 29. Tingstjg. i Hall. n. doms. 29-32, anst. å William Kristensens Advibyrå i Gbg 32-44, deläg. där sed. 44. Omb :man f. Motormänn. riksförb. sed. 40, led. av styr. f. ett flert. bol. o. fastigh ifören., v. ordf. i Gbgs lawntenniskl. sed. 40, led. av styr. f. Bachelor’s club. Led. av Svies advisamf. sed. 34. Hobbies i tennis o. segling. *Forsgren, Erik Abraham, sanato-rieiäkare, med. dr, Svenshögen, f. 13/ 9/96 i Falun av bergsing. Oskar F. o. Malin Jurell. G. 21 m. tandläk., med. kand. Hertha Lundquist. Barn i se
translated:
Forssenius, Gunnar Torsten, lawyer, Gothenburg, born December 30, 1903 in Gothenburg to builder Johannes Andersson and Anna Andersson-Forssenius. Married to Dagmar Sjöbring in 1942. Children: Lars, born in 1943, and Maud, born in 1944. Studied in Gothenburg, receiving a degree in 1923, and a law degree in Uppsala in 1929. Served in the Halland district court from 1929 to 1932 and was employed at William Kristensen's Law Office in Gothenburg from 1932 to 1944, becoming a co-owner in 1944. He was a trustee for the National Motorist Association from 1940 and a member of the board of several companies and real estate associations. Vice-chairman of the Gothenburg Lawn Tennis Club since 1940, and a member of the board of the Bachelor's Club. Member of the Swedish Law Society since 1934. Hobbies include tennis and sailing. 

*Forsgren, Erik Abraham, sanatorium physician, medical doctor, and holder of a doctorate in medicine, born September 13, 1896 in Falun to mining engineer Oskar F. and Malin Jurell. Married to dentist and medical student Hertha Lundquist in 1921. Children are not mentioned in this text.
